{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://code.google.com/p/better-oblivion-sorting-software/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul\cf1 http://code.google.com/p/better-oblivion-sorting-software/}}}\f0\fs24\par
\line Files on Nexus are updated once a week or so. Always use latest dated files.\line\line\line\ul\fs27 ADDITIONAL FILES: \ulnone\fs24\line\line FCOM-only masterlist.txt database file. Using it instead of the normal one will move all FCOM files to the start in the correct order (and check for problems, show comments as usual) but leave all other mods' load order the same as before running BOSS. Useful for troubleshooting purposes and useful to anyone who wants to keep their existing mod load order then add FCOM and finalise everything by hand. This file is getting very old but it does the job (sort of).\line\line\line\ul\fs27 CREDITS:\ulnone\fs24\line\line Sources for the mod list and its order include: Agiel's Annotated Load Order; Fivefries load order; dev_akm's official expanded FCOM load order (FCOM 0.9.9); suggestions and instructions from Mart's Monster Mod, Better Cities, Open Cities and Open Better Cities developers; suggestions and instructions from many other modders; lots of advice and information from users. Some people have gone out of their way and provided continuing, expert and detailed help - thank you very much!\line\line Thanks go to Wrye for implementing the importing of BOSS's Bashed Patch tag suggestions into {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://wrye.ufrealms.net/Wrye%20Bash.html" }}{\fldrslt{\cf1\ul Wrye Bash}}}\cf0\ulnone\f0\fs24 .\line\line\line\ul\fs27 PROJECT MEMBERS\ulnone\fs24\line\line BOSS since the middle of 2009 has been a collaborative project on Google Code using the SVN version tracking and editing engine. In alphabetical order:\line\line\b Google Code Administrators: \b0\par
